[Infection with _trichinella_ is widespread in South America including Argentina. Pigs exposed to the environment may be infected by feeding kitchen waste or eating infected rodents. Pigs should be tested for _trichinella_ before used in local products either consumed within the family nor sold at markets.

HealthMap location Junin de los Andes: http://healthmap.org/r/2msn, and Villa Maria http://healthmap.org/r/2mso. - Mod.EP]
